macro_markets.query: What are the most important macroeconomic and stock market news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major index movements, Fed/central bank news, and significant company earnings or announcements.

items.title: S&P 500, Dow and Nasdaq close near records as year-end rally continues
items.summary: Major U.S. indexes were roughly flat to slightly up in the past 24 hours as a late-year ‘Santa Claus’ rally and AI-related gains kept markets supported; the S&P 500 closed around 6,930 while the Nasdaq and Dow showed modest moves amid light holiday volume, with new highs outpacing new lows on the NYSE but more declines on the Nasdaq[1][3].

items.title: S&P 500 poised to test 7,000 as year-end momentum persists
items.summary: Analysts noted the S&P 500 was about 1% from the 7,000 level and on track for a multi-month winning streak, driven largely by tech and AI leadership despite recent sector rotation and thin trading volumes[4][3].

items.title: Nvidia rises after licensing deal with Groq; AI names support market
items.summary: Nvidia gained after announcing a licensing arrangement with AI chip startup Groq and hiring Groq’s CEO, a development that helped lift AI-related equities and underpinned broader market strength[1][3].

items.title: Gold, silver hit fresh records; miners rally
items.summary: Precious metals reached new highs in the past 24 hours, boosting U.S.-listed miners such as First Majestic, Coeur Mining and Endeavour Silver, which rose between about 1–3% amid the metal price strength[1].

items.title: U.S. economic data showing stronger growth boosts year-end optimism
items.summary: Recent GDP and other economic releases showed stronger-than-expected growth (including a robust Q3 revision highlighted in weekly market commentary), a factor investors cited for both encouraging risk appetite and keeping attention on Fed policy paths[2].

items.title: Global markets mixed in holiday-thinned trading
items.summary: Major international indices showed mixed opening moves—Asia markets were mixed with small gains in Hong Kong and Shanghai, while European and U.S. markets saw limited or no trading due to holiday schedules, reflecting subdued volumes and narrower breadth worldwide[5][1].

crypto_news.query: What are the most significant cryptocurrency and blockchain news from the past 24 hours? Include major price movements, regulatory news, and notable project developments.

items.title: Bitcoin rises above $90,000 amid geopolitical uncertainty
items.summary: Bitcoin climbed over 2% to trade above $90,000 as hopes for a Russia–Ukraine peace deal faded, pushing risk assets higher; major cryptocurrencies including ether and XRP also moved with the market uptick.

items.title: Analysts warn of ‘hidden bear market’ despite possible 2025 highs for Bitcoin
items.summary: Market analysts suggested that Bitcoin might reach new highs in 2025 but finish the year lower — a scenario described as a ‘hidden bear market’ — while reporting that surface calm masks deeper turbulence in crypto markets.

items.title: Large token unlocks scheduled around year-end — HYPE, SUI, KMNO among biggest
items.summary: Blockchain token unlock schedules show sizeable releases in late December and early January, including a ~9.92M HYPE unlock (≈$256M), a ~43.69M SUI unlock (~9.74% of supply, ≈$14.4M), and a large Kamino (KMNO) unlock, raising concerns about potential sell pressure.

items.title: Ripple moves tens of millions of XRP to unknown address; community watches for intent
items.summary: Blockchain monitors reported a large Ripple transfer involving 65 million XRP (over $120M), prompting speculation about on‑chain treasury management or market activity by the company.

items.title: Midnight’s NIGHT token shows extreme early volume and outperformance claims from Cardano founder
items.summary: The newly launched Midnight network token NIGHT has seen explosive trading volume and has been touted by Cardano founder Charles Hoskinson as outperforming tokens such as XRP and Solana shortly after launch.

items.title: Crypto ETFs continue to attract assets despite year‑to‑date drawdowns
items.summary: Bitcoin ETFs have drawn significant inflows in 2025 — for example, BlackRock’s IBIT has taken in over $25B this year and holds about $66B — showing sustained investor demand for ETF wrappers even amid poor short‑term performance.

ai_news.query: What are the most important artificial intelligence and machine learning news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include new model releases, company announcements, research breakthroughs, and industry trends.

items.title: MIT and Recursion Release Boltz-2 AI Model for Protein Structure and Binding Prediction
items.summary: Researchers at MIT and Recursion announced Boltz-2, an updated AI model that predicts protein structures and drug binding affinities in 20 seconds using a single GPU. The model is available under an MIT license for commercial and non-commercial use.

items.title: Meta AI Unveils Pixio Image Model Excelling in 3D Reconstruction
items.summary: Meta AI released Pixio, a 631-million-parameter image model that outperforms larger models like DINOv3 in depth estimation, 3D reconstruction, and robot learning tasks through simple pixel reconstruction training on 2 billion web images.

items.title: MIT Develops AI-Driven Robotic System for Verbal Object Assembly
items.summary: Engineers at MIT created an AI-powered robotic assembly system that builds objects based on verbal instructions from users.

items.title: Google DeepMind Co-Founder Predicts AI Will End Work-from-Home
items.summary: Shane Legg, co-founder of Google DeepMind, warned that advancing AI will eliminate remote cognitive jobs by enabling smaller teams to achieve superior results, fundamentally altering the economy.

items.title: FWD Expands AI Capabilities for Insurance Claims Processing
items.summary: Insurance company FWD enhanced its AI-assisted Smart Operations with machine learning, achieving 97.2% accuracy in low-risk claims, boosting fraud detection to 52%, and improving customer satisfaction; expansion planned across markets.

items.title: Google Shares 40 AI Tips for Search, Photos, and Gemini Apps
items.summary: Google released a list of 40 AI-focused tips to help users maximize value from its products including Search, Photos, and Gemini.

gaming.query: What are the most notable video game and gaming industry news from the past 24 hours? Include game releases, announcements, esports, and industry developments.

items.title: Epic Games Store free game: SKALD — Against the Black Priory (Dec 28–29 free)
items.summary: Epic Games Store has revealed SKALD: Against the Black Priory as its free title for the December 28–29 giveaway window.

items.title: Nicktoons & The Dice of Destiny PS5 review published
items.summary: A review of Nicktoons & The Dice of Destiny on PS5 evaluates the game as a nostalgia-driven isometric ARPG with solid licensed fan service but limited level variety and questionable value at full price.

items.title: Donot blockchain game posts Daily Combo highlights for Dec 28–29
items.summary: Donot — a blockchain-based game launched in December 2024 — published its Daily Combo (in-game daily missions and rewards) update for December 28–29 as part of ongoing airdrop and reward programs.

items.title: Tomarket publishes Daily Combo update for Dec 28–29
items.summary: Tomarket's community-focused site Bittime posted the Tomarket Daily Combo update and guides for Dec 28–29, covering daily emoji-combo challenges and token reward strategies.

items.title: EarnBet launches crypto casino supporting 14+ currencies
items.summary: EarnBet announced the launch of an online crypto casino expanding support to more than 14 cryptocurrencies, marking an industry development at the intersection of gaming and crypto gambling.

tech_news.query: What are the most important technology news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major product launches, company news, and significant tech industry developments. Exclude AI-specific news.

items.title: PARAM Rudra Supercomputer Launched at IIT-Patna
items.summary: India unveiled the PARAM Rudra supercomputer, a state-of-the-art High-Performance Computing system, at IIT-Patna in Bihar on December 26, marking the first such installation in the state.

items.title: BIS Notifies India's First Standard for Bomb Disposal Systems
items.summary: The Bureau of Indian Standards notified India's first dedicated standard (IS 19412:2025) for bomb disposal systems to enhance security infrastructure.

items.title: Therabody Offers 30% Discount on Recovery Tech Devices
items.summary: Therabody is providing up to 30% off on its science-backed wellness and recovery technology devices this month.
items.source: Daily Tech Hacker News via Wired

items.title: US Court Blocks 3D-Printed Gun Plans Sale
items.summary: A federal judge in Seattle temporarily blocked plans for manufacturing firearms via 3D printers, halting an agreement by Defense Distributed to sell online designs for plastic or metal guns.
